Create migration file `backend/migrations/versions/20260104_xxxx_add_wordpress_draft_fields.py` with SQL commands:
```sql
ALTER TABLE worklist_items ADD COLUMN wordpress_draft_url VARCHAR(500);
ALTER TABLE worklist_items ADD COLUMN wordpress_draft_uploaded_at TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE;
ALTER TABLE worklist_items ADD COLUMN wordpress_post_id INTEGER;
```
Ensure all fields are nullable and include appropriate comments. Test migration in development environment to verify schema changes are applied correctly.

Create `frontend/src/components/ArticleReview/PublishSuccessConfirmation.tsx`:
```typescript
interface PublishSuccessConfirmationProps {
    articleTitle: string;
    wordpressDraftUrl: string;
    uploadedAt: string;
    wordpressPostId: number;
    screenshot?: string;
    onClose: () => void;
    onOpenWordPress: () => void;
}
```
Implement UI layout with:
- Success header with checkmark
- Screenshot display (clickable to enlarge)
- WordPress draft information section
- Clickable WordPress URL
- Upload timestamp formatting
- Next steps guidance
- Action buttons (Open WordPress, Close)
Use existing ScreenshotGallery component for screenshot display.

